<h2 id="_creating_an_ebay_promotion">1. Creating an eBay promotion</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Running promotions is a great way to attract more customers and increase basket size.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Find out more about eBay promotions in the following video tutorial:</p>
</div>
<div class="videoblock">
<div class="title">eBay promotions</div>
<div class="content">
<iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/240810586" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the menu <strong>Listings » eBay Promotions</strong> to create promotions.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating promotions:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Listings » eBay Promotions</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Create new promotion</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings for the sections <strong>Basic settings</strong>, <strong>Rules</strong> and <strong>Inventory</strong> as described in <a href="#ebay-marketing-campaigns">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The promotion is saved but not yet started.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
